{{TennisEventInfo|1975|Monte Carlo WCT| | date= 23 – 30 March | edition=70th | category=[[World Championship Tennis]] (WCT) | prize_money=$60,000 | draw=32S/16D | surface=[[Clay court|Clay]] / outdoor | location=[[Monte Carlo]], [[Monaco]] | venue=[[Monte Carlo Country Club]] | champs={{flagicon|ESP|1945}} [[Manuel Orantes]] <ref name="ms">{{cite web|title=1975 Monte Carlo WCT Men's Singles draw|url=http://www.atpworldtour.com/en/scores/archive/monte-carlo/410/1975/draws?matchType=singles|website=www.atpworldtour.com|publisher=[[Association of Tennis Professionals]] (ATP)}}</ref> | champd={{flagicon|RSA|1928}} [[Bob Hewitt]] / {{flagicon|RSA|1928}} [[Frew McMillan]] <ref name=md>{{cite web|title=ATP – 1975 Monte Carlo WCT Men's Doubles draw|url=http://www.atpworldtour.com/Share/Event-Draws.aspx?Year=1975&EventId=410&Draw=md|publisher=ATP}}</ref> | after_name=Monte Carlo Open | main_name=Monte-Carlo Masters {{!}} Monte Carlo WCT }}
The '''1975 Monte Carlo WCT''', also known by its sponsored name '''Marlboro Classic''', was a men's [[tennis]] tournament played on [[Clay court|outdoor clay courts]] at the [[Monte Carlo Country Club]] in [[Monte Carlo]], [[Monaco]]. The tournament was part of the Green Group of the [[1975 World Championship Tennis circuit]]. It was the 70th edition of the event and was held from 23 March through 30 March 1975. [[Manuel Orantes]] won the singles title.<ref name=wot76>{{cite book|title=World of Tennis '76 : a BP and Commercial Union yearbook|year=1976|publisher=Queen Anne Press|location=London|isbn=9780362002768|oclc=650229036|pages=144,150|editor=[[John Barrett (tennis)|John Barrett]]}}</ref>
==Champions== ===Singles===
{{flagicon|ESP|1945}} '''[[Manuel Orantes ]]''' defeated {{flagicon|RSA|1928}} [[Bob Hewitt]] 6–2, 6–4
===Doubles===
{{flagicon|RSA|1928}} '''[[Bob Hewitt]] / {{flagicon|RSA|1928}} [[Frew McMillan]]''' defeated {{flagicon|USA}} [[Arthur Ashe]] / {{flagicon|NED}} [[Tom Okker]] 6–3, 6–2
