The '''Battle of Coffrane''' took place on February 28, 1296, about 1 km to the east of [[Coffrane, Switzerland|Coffrane]] in the [[Cantons of Switzerland|canton]] of [[Neuchâtel (canton)|Neuchâtel]]. The Lords of [[Valangin]] with support from the [[Roman Catholic Diocese of Basel|Bishop of Basel]] rebelled against the Count of [[Neuchâtel]].<ref>{{HDS|2859|Coffrane}}</ref> The battle was fought in the [[Val-de-Ruz]], next to the village of Coffrane. The Count of Neuchâtel, Rollin, won the battle.<ref>{{cite book |title=Sozialdisziplinierung - Verfahren - Bürokraten: Entstehung und Entwicklung der modernen Verwaltung |last=Pfister |first=Ulrich |author2=Maurice de Tribolet |page=51 |year=1999 |publisher=Schwabe |isbn=978-3-7965-1352-7 }}</ref>

