{{Politics of the European Union mini}} The '''Environment Council''' (ENV) is a configuration of the [[Council of the European Union]]. <ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.consilium.europa.eu/en/council-eu/|title=The Council of the European Union - Consilium|publisher=|accessdate=26 February 2017}}</ref> It meets about four times a year. It brings together the [[Environment minister|environment ministers]] and is responsible for the [[Environmental policy of the European Union|EU environment policy]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://europa.eu/pol/env/index_en.htm|title=Environment - European Union website, the official EU website - European Commission|first=|last=Anonymous|date=16 June 2016|publisher=|accessdate=26 February 2017}}</ref>
This Council deals with [[environmental protection]], climate change, prudent use of resources and protection of human health.
In this regard, the Council adopts legislation together with the [[European Parliament]] in relation to:
*protection of natural habitats *clean air and water *proper [[Waste management|waste disposal]] *toxic chemicals *[[sustainable economy]]
