The '''Europe Gate''' is a [[sculpture]] made out of [[LiTraCon]], or Light Transmitting Concrete. It is a wall 3.5 meters squared and commemorates [[Hungary]] joining the [[European Union]]. It was built in 2004 in [[Fort Monostor]] in the town of [[Komárom]]<ref>https://www.slideshare.net/abidalimahar52/original-litracon accessed July 12th, 2018</ref> by Áron Losonczi & Orsolya Vadász.<ref>http://www.litracon.hu/datasheet.php?id=9</ref>

