{{italic title}}
'''''Idou o anthropos''''' ([[Ancient Greek]]: Ἰδοὺ ὁ ἄνθρωπος; ''[[Ecce homo]]'' or ''Behold the Man''), written in 1886, is a work by poet and writer [[Andreas Laskaratos]].<ref>{{cite book|last=Beaton|first=Roderick|edition=2nd|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=QI9Xw7EiIjsC&pg=PA52|title=An introduction to modern Greek literature|publisher=Oxford University Press|page=52|year=1999|origyear=first published 1994|isbn=0-19-815974-9|accessdate=October 27, 2009}}</ref> The main theme of the book is human characters and through a series of examples it tries to acquaint the reader with the different attributes of the human psyche in its different manifestations.

The multitude of different characters portrayed in the book are an early attempt to categorize people according to their personality traits.

