{{Infobox organization | name = Kiro Congo | image = | size = 250px | caption = | abbreviation= KCD | formation = 11 November 1947 | type = Congolese non-profit youth organization | location = {{Flag|DRC}} | purpose = Catholic youth organization | headquarters = {{Flag|DRC}} | membership = 55,000 | leader_title2 = Presidents | leader_name2 = | leader_title3 = Praeses | leader_name3 = | leader_title4 = Secretary-General | leader_name4 = | website = }}
The '''Kiro Congo''' ('''KCD''') is a Catholic youth organization in the [[Democratic Republic of Congo]].<ref name=":0">{{Cite web|url=http://kiro-republique-democratique-du-congo.e-monsite.com/|title=KIRO CONGO/KIPUSHI est une association sans but lucratif|website=kiro-republique-democratique-du-congo.e-monsite.com|access-date=2016-06-09}}</ref> It is one of the important big youth movements in the country.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.memoireonline.com/08/11/4713/m_Leglise-catholique-et-le-developpement-de-la-ville-de-kolwezicas-du-diocese-de-kolwezi16.html|title=Memoire Online - L'eglise catholique et le developpement de la ville de kolwezi(cas du diocese de kolwezi) - Nickson KALUME TAMBWE|website=Memoire Online|access-date=2016-09-11}}</ref> Kiro Congo is a member of the Catholic umbrella of youth organizations [[Fimcap]].<ref name=":2" /><ref name=":3">{{Cite journal|last=Rompaey|first=Lies Van|date=1995-01-01|title=The Development of the Catholic Youth Organizations in the Belgian Congo (1908–1960)|url=https://dx.doi.org/10.1080/00309230.1995.11434845|journal=Paedagogica Historica|volume=31|issue=sup1|pages=193–212|doi=10.1080/00309230.1995.11434845|issn=0030-9230}}</ref>
==History== Kiro was founded on 11 November 1947.<ref name=":0" /><ref name=":2">{{Cite web|url=http://fimcap.org/en/africa/kiro-congo|title=Kiro Congo|website=fimcap.org|access-date=2016-06-09}}</ref> The youth movement grew quickly in the 1950s. In 1957 already about 150 Kiro groups existed in the [[Democratic Republic of Congo]].<ref name=":3" /><ref>Peeters, A., directeur national du mouvement Chiro (Federations des Patronages) en Belgique (1957); Rapport de Ia reunion intervicariale des detegues du mouvement Chiro, organisee a Kabwe du 29 au 31 decembre, a /'occasion du voyage de Monsieur /'abbe, Chiro Archives 11. 1.3. </ref> In 1960 Kiro had already about 240 boys' and girls' groups with approximately 17,000 individual members.<ref name=":3" />
==Organization== Kiro Congo is structured in the following sections (based on age-groups):<ref name=":1">{{Cite web|url=http://www.kjg.de/index.php?id=295|title=Kiro Kongo|website=www.kjg.de|access-date=2016-06-09}}</ref><ref name=":4">{{Cite web|url=http://www.bloggen.be/congo/archief.php?ID=20|title=Het leven zoals het is: Congo!|website=www.bloggen.be|access-date=2016-09-11}}</ref> {| class="wikitable sortable" |- !Age group !Name of section |- |6 – 12 years |"(Pré-) Bakayouki" |- |12 – 14 years |"Youpi" |- |14 – 16 years |"Gens" |- |16 years and older |"Aspis" |}
==Activities== * Meetings in local groups * Games, songs, sports, dancing * Pastoral and spiritual activities on Saturday and Sunday * Educational activities<ref name=":1" /> * International partnerships<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.allesoverjeugd.be/nieuws/chiro-sluit-een-partnerschap-met-kiro-congo|title=Chiro sluit een partnerschap met Kiro Congo.|last=|first=|date=|website=Alles over jeugd (website of the Flamish youth representation "De Ambrassade")|publisher=|access-date=2016-09-11}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://chiro.be/nieuws/2007/09/17/partnerschap-met-kiro-congo%25E2%2580%25A6|title=Nieuws|last=|first=|date=|website=|publisher=Chirojeugd Vlaanderen|access-date=2016-09-11}}</ref>
== Intercontinental cooperation == * The work of Kiro Congo is supported by the Flamish NGO [[Broederlijk Delen]].<ref name=":4" /> * Kiro Congo is a member of the Catholic umbrella of youth organizations [[Fimcap]].<ref name=":2" /><ref name=":3" />
