'''Kosovo''' has participated in the [[Turkvision Song Contest]] once since its debut in {{Tscyr|2013}}.<ref name="Participation">{{cite web|last=Granger|first=Anthony|title=Participating Countries Revealed|url=http://eurovoix.com/2013/10/19/turkvizyon-2013-participating-countries-revealed/|publisher=Eurovoix|accessdate=25 October 2013|date=19 October 2013}}</ref> The Kosovan broadcaster, [[Radio Television of Kosovo]] (RTK), has been the organiser of the Kosovan entry since its debut in the contest.  In 2013, Kosovo's first entry at Turkvision, [[Ergin Karahasan]] which belongs to the Turkish minority in Kosovo, qualified to the grand final were the finished in 12th place with a score of 151 points.  Kosovo withdrew from the [[Turkvision Song Contest 2014|2014 contest]] because the country is not recognised by Russia, therefore entrance would have been denied. Instead, Albania entered the contest.

==History==
[[Republic of Kosovo|Kosovo]] made their debut in the [[Turkvision Song Contest]] at the [[Turkvision Song Contest 2013|2013]] festival, in [[Eskişehir]], [[Turkey]].<ref name="Participation"/>  An updated participation list was published on 10 September 2014, of which Kosovo did not appear as participating, although it is unknown as to why they do not show on the list.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Granger|first1=Anthony|title=Turkvizyon’14: Germany To Debut!|url=http://eurovoix.com/2014/09/10/turkvizyon14-germany-to-debut/|website=Turkvizyon.tv|publisher=Eurovoix.com|accessdate=30 September 2014|date=10 September 2014|quote=The list means that the following countries are either withdrawing or are yet to confirm their participation}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Yarışmaya Katılan Ülkeler|url=http://turkvizyon.tv/yarismacilar.html|website=turkvizyon.tv|publisher=Turkvizyon.tv|accessdate=30 September 2014|language=Turkish|trans-title=The participating countries}}</ref>

