{{Infobox museum | name = KØS Museum of art in public spaces | image = KØS Museum for kunst i det offentlige rum.jpg | caption = The building viewed from Nørregade | alt = | map_type = | map_caption = | map_alt = | established = | collection = | area = | location = Nørregade 29, [[Køge]], [[Denmark]] | visitors = | publictransit = |director = Ulrikke Neergaard | coordinates = {{coord|55.458828|12.183414|region:DK|display=inline,title}} | website = [http://www.koes.dk/en Official website] }} '''KØS Museum of art in public spaces''' is situated in Nørregade in [[Køge]], [[Denmark]]. It is the only museum in Denmark focusing of art in the public realm. It boasts a collection of models and sketches for public artworks and plays host to special exhibitions about the subject. Its permanent exhibition includes the original plaster model for the Little Mermaid in Copenhagen and the cartoons for the Queen’s tapestries in the [[Christiansborg|Danish parliament]] by [[Bjørn Nørgaard]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.copenhagencard.com/attractions/391/K%C3%98S%20Museum%20of%20art%20in%20public%20spaces|title=KØS Museum of art in public spaces|language=Danish|publisher=Copenhagen Card|accessdate=5 September 2016}}</ref>
The museum opened in 1977 under the name Køge Skitsesamling (Køge Sketch Collection). Its building was adapted in 2001 by local architectural firm Køge Arkitekterne.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.arkark.dk/building.aspx?buildingid=2552|title=Køge Skitsesamling|language=Danish|website=arkark.dk|accessdate=5 September 2016}}</ref> In 2009, the museum adopted its current name.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.pressreader.com/denmark/politiken/20090119/281788509941523|title=Nyt navn til skitsesamling|language=Danish|website=pressreader.com|accessdate=5 September 2016}}</ref>
