{{Notability|date=January 2017}} {{infobox weapon | name = M59/85 | image = | image_size = | alt = | caption = Helmet | origin = [[Yugoslavia]], [[Serbia]], [[Croatia]], | type = [[Combat helmet]]
<!-- Service history --> | service = 1959 - 2000 | used_by = [[Yugoslav People's Army|JNA]], Serbian Army | wars = [[Yugoslav Wars]] <!-- General specifications -->
| weight = {{convert|2.2|kg|lb|abbr=on}}
}}
The M59/M85 is a Yugoslavian [[Combat helmet]]. They were produced in 1958 and 1985 as the names suggest.
The helmet's shape was based on [[Stahlhelm]] (M35) previously used by the Yugoslav army.
The helmets are made of [[Steel]] and have a partly leather liner and there are many covers for this helmet. One of the covers is a net-mask, which was used by Yugoslav marines. Furthermore, the helmets often had stars or Yugoslavian decals/stickers <ref>https://colemans.com/shop/militaria/misc-militaria-gallery/m59-85-helmet-assortment/</ref>
The M85 Is a more modern helmet and has a smaller rear/ear guard.<ref>http://brendonshelmets.weebly.com/yugoslavia-m59.html</ref> Some M85 were made of [[Kevlar]] giving the wearer much more protection. These helmets were the main helmets of separatist fighters in the [[Yugoslav Wars]] <ref>http://brendonshelmets.weebly.com/yugoslavia-m59.html, 3rd paragraph</ref>
